</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm105355104">
<problem id="fs-idm105354848">
<para id="fs-idm146630688">How much solid NaCH<sub>3</sub>CO<sub>2</sub>•3H<sub>2</sub>O must be added to 0.300 L of a 0.50-<emphasis effect="italics">M</emphasis> acetic acid solution to give a buffer with a pH of 5.00? (Hint: Assume a negligible change in volume as the solid is added.)</para>
