</problem>
<solution id="fs-idm84079584">
<para id="fs-idp147776">(a) pH = 5.222;<newline/>
(b) The solution is acidic.<newline/>
(c) pH = 5.221</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm111629776">
<problem id="fs-idm104905504">
<para id="fs-idm104905248">A 5.36–g sample of NH<sub>4</sub>Cl was added to 25.0 mL of 1.00 <emphasis effect="italics">M</emphasis> NaOH and the resulting solution</para>
<para id="fs-idm2218160">diluted to 0.100 L.</para>
<para id="fs-idm105728688">(a) What is the pH of this buffer solution?</para>
<para id="fs-idm105728304">(b) Is the solution acidic or basic?</para>
<para id="fs-idm105727920">(c) What is the pH of a solution that results when 3.00 mL of 0.034 <emphasis effect="italics">M</emphasis> HCl is added to the solution?</para>
</problem>
