<glossary>
<definition id="fs-idp88494848"><term>buffer capacity</term> <meaning id="fs-idp88495360">amount of an acid or base that can be added to a volume of a buffer solution before its pH changes significantly (usually by one pH unit)</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-idp88495904"><term>buffer</term> <meaning id="fs-idp88496416">mixture of a weak acid or a weak base and the salt of its conjugate; the pH of a buffer resists change when small amounts of acid or base are added</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-idm71412016"><term>Henderson-Hasselbalch equation</term> <meaning id="fs-idm71411504">equation used to calculate the pH of buffer solutions</meaning></definition>
</glossary>
